title_full:
Ton Lebbink

              —
              Wat Doe Je Met Me?
            
              (RUBBER)
label: RUBBER
description:
Choice cuts of odd Euro body music from Dutch legend Lebbink’s ‘90s house phase surface for 1st time on the Rubber sublabel of BAKK, ripe for heads into Dirk DeSaever’s new beat, Rudi Huybrechts’ EBM, or the noir bops of Victor De Roo and Stroom.

title_full:
Ailie Ormston and Tim Fraser

              —
              It Changes
            
              (Bison Records)
label: Bison Records
description:
Absolutely crackers material from Ailie Ormston and Tim Fraser that shunts UK dance themes through broken cultural motifs, field recordings and chillingly plastic General MIDI instrumentation. One part James Ferarro, one part Theo Burt, one part Farmers Manual?

In an attempt to portray the labyrinth of post-neoliberal British culture in the 2020s, Ormston... more

title_full:
Dim Garden

            —
            Elle Tombe la Lune

label: Osàre! Editions
description:
Elena Colombi’s Osàre! Editions complete a strong ’22 program with Emil Valev’s first volley of dark, fizzing, avant new wave landing on the senses like a fantasy adjunct to Suicide, Uri Katzenstein, Victor De Roo.

This is the first release, proper, by the deep Euro wave outlier. It’s an open invitation to his worldbuilding style, splicing rugged post-industrial/darkwave... more

Romance Relic

            Breakwater Of A Veiled Heart

label: Muscut
description:
Serene, space loungey new age synth fluff from Ukraine’s Arthur Mine, on the line between early 0PN, Sven Grünberg and Vangelis

‘Urania’ captures two works from Arthur’s ‘Dispersed Mind’ (2021, Sine Language Records) 12” alongside all new and exclusive work to portray a most bucolic/cosmic-optimist grasp of what matters in new age synth music. Lovers... more
